title: feat: add invert option to base_def for flipping cad model
description: Adds an optional boolean property invert to the base_def schema to hint for flipping headers in jscad-electronics.
body:
This pull request adds a new optional boolean property to the `base_def` schema in `src/helpers/zod/base_def.ts`. This property, `invert`, is intended as a hint to `jscad-electronics` that headers should be flipped.

* Schema update:
  * Added an optional `invert` boolean property to the `base_def` zod schema, with a description indicating it is a hint for flipping headers in `jscad-electronics`.

Ref: [maybe you could look into this? We need to add it to footprinter but it doesn't change the footprint, it's just there to hint to jscad-electronics that the headers should be flipped, lmk](https://discord.com/channels/1233487248129921135/1439482849920286723/1439484290642481233)

title: Fix tearing in all components when pcb is transparent in Mainfold
description: Fixes z-fighting artifacts in 3D geometry rendering by enabling polygon offset for mesh materials and updates the jscad-electronics package version to the latest.

The most important changes are: Dependency update: * Updated the `jscad-electronics` package version from `^0.0.89` to `^0.0.91` in `package.json` to bring in the latest fixes or features. Rendering improvements: * In `src/utils/manifold/create-three-geometry-meshes.ts`, enabled `polygonOffset` with negative factors for mesh materials to help prevent z-fighting artifacts when rendering overlapping surfaces. /fix #568 ## Before ## After

title: feat: add invert functionality to PinRow component and example usage
description: Adds support for rendering inverted pin row footprints in the 3D visualization components by detecting the invert parameter and flipping Z coordinates in the PinRow component.
body: This pull request introduces support for rendering inverted pin row footprints in the 3D visualization components. The main changes include detecting the `invert` parameter in footprint strings, updating the `PinRow` component to handle inversion by flipping Z coordinates, and adding a snapshot test to verify correct rendering of inverted pin rows. **Support for inverted pin row footprints:** * Added logic in `Footprinter3d.tsx` to detect the `_invert` parameter in footprint strings and pass an `invert` prop to the `PinRow` component. [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-8ef5003688394a782da38d10f8dd9c9ece9af16db5a43ce66b655e6c19bb0bc9R75-R77) [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-8ef5003688394a782da38d10f8dd9c9ece9af16db5a43ce66b655e6c19bb0bc9L175-R184) * Updated the `PinRow` component in `PinRow.tsx` to accept an `invert` prop and flip Z coordinates for all relevant 3D objects when inversion is enabled, ensuring correct visual orientation. [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-b437df9b77b641cb7c8494f5bc3f5c9029fa7568c05cd37cd4923e86900fdd4dL1-R28) [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-b437df9b77b641cb7c8494f5bc3f5c9029fa7568c05cd37cd4923e86900fdd4dL35-R41) [[3]](diffhunk://#diff-b437df9b77b641cb7c8494f5bc3f5c9029fa7568c05cd37cd4923e86900fdd4dL45-R55) [[4]](diffhunk://#diff-b437df9b77b641cb7c8494f5bc3f5c9029fa7568c05cd37cd4923e86900fdd4dL55-R69) [[5]](diffhunk://#diff-b437df9b77b641cb7c8494f5bc3f5c9029fa7568c05cd37cd4923e86900fdd4dL64-R78) **Testing:** * Added a new snapshot test in `pinrow6-invert.test.ts` to verify that the inverted pin row footprint is rendered correctly. **Examples:** * Added a new example file `fp-pinrow6-invert.example.tsx` to demonstrate rendering of an inverted 6-pin row footprint. ## Example pinrow6 (without `invert` in footprint) ## Example pinrow6-invert (with `invert` in footprint) /fix #229

description: Fixes the issue where the CadViewer component does not re-render correctly when toggling fullscreen mode by adding a key prop based on the isFullScreen state.

title: Support kicad_mod files loading for tsci add 'url'
description: Adds support for loading .kicad_mod files by converting absolute file paths to file: URLs for Buns fetch, enhancing platform configuration with KiCad parsing support.
body:
1. Get a complete platform config from eval with KiCad parsing support and any user overrides.
2. This handles the conversion of absolute file paths to file:// URLs for Bun's fetch.
3. When Bun imports a .kicad_mod file, it returns an absolute path like "/path/to/file.kicad_mod".
4. The default loadFromUrl expects a URL, so we wrap it to convert paths to file:// URLs.

body:
## How GapFillSubSolver Works

GapFillSubSolver operates as a post-processing cleanup algorithm that creates **brand new rectangles** to fill empty spaces left after the main RectDiff placement. It follows a four-stage process:

1. **SCAN**: Detects uncovered areas using grid-based sweep-line algorithm, merging adjacent empty cells into maximal gap rectangles
2. **SELECT**: Prioritizes gaps by size and multi-layer coverage, choosing the most valuable gap to fill next
3. **EXPAND**: Places seed point at gap center and grows a rectangle outward until hitting existing rectangles, obstacles, or boundaries
4. **PLACE**: Adds the successfully expanded rectangle to the solution as a new placement

## Fundamental Difference from RectDiff

**RectDiff** solves the **routing problem** - it places rectangles to enable electrical signal connections based on circuit topology and routing requirements from SimpleRouteJson input.

**GapFillSubSolver** solves the **coverage problem** - it maximizes board area utilization by filling leftover empty spaces with new rectangles, regardless of routing needs.

**RectDiff** creates rectangles for **electrical functionality** (routing paths), while **GapFillSubSolver** creates rectangles for **geometric efficiency** (space utilization). They serve complementary but entirely different purposes in the placement pipeline: connectivity versus coverage optimization.
